Firstly manager uses the gym as her own personal gym to run her own personal trainer business training her clients together with her partner. Always hogging multiple equipment and machines and talking laughing so loudly!

Secondly they are not even promoting the AF pt sessions and illegally pushing her own agenda. Was told off by her staff when I was just help my friend correcting her stating no coaching was allowed when I‚Äôm not even a PT and just barely helping my friend.

Staff don‚Äôt give a damn about gym equipment cause everything I visit the weights and plates are all over when they are 2-3 staff and nobody bothers to arrange it back properly. Why are you getting paid again?

Finally, they had a renovation taking away all shower , toilet and changing room facilities. It‚Äôs been 2 days since they promised the end of construction so when I went in to workout, after my training I asked the staff where to shower and change one of the male staff had the audacity to ask me to change in the locker area which was an open area next to the water cooler and near the lockers accessible to both men and women. author: Nickson Wong
text:
I had 2 training session with Kal at Anytime Fitness Keppel branch (1 hour each), and I would personally recommend him. Kal has been incredibly professional, knowledgeable, and approachable. He really take into account of my request and prepare me for long endurance hiking by designing the training session to fit my goals and fitness level. He listens carefully and more than happy to guide me through each workout and always makes sure I‚Äôm pushing myself to the limit without overexerting (which may result in injury in worst case scenario).

Both session with Kal has been challenging but also enjoyable as he always takes the time to explain the purpose behind each exercise and how it may affect my hiking capacity in the long run. He‚Äôs also very attentive during my workout session, correcting my posture and making sure I'm not injure during my workout.

Additionally, the staff here is very friendly, welcoming, and professional. But I must say, please avoid peak period like 6pm-7pm it was quite crowded, though I supposed it is normal since that's the time everyone left their work and just getting into exercise for the day.

If you‚Äôre looking for a personal trainer who truly cares, and able to cater the training according to your need please look for Kal from the Keppel branch team!

author: Daniel Ng
text:
Very small gym but gets the job done. Equipments are all clean, new and well maintained. The cardio machines all face a floor to ceiling window with natural light which is nice. Machines are all Precor branded. 2 squat racks, 1 deadlift platform and 1 smith machine. Dumbbells go up to 45kg and there's enough variety to have a decent workout.

Went in at 7.30am on a Wednesday and there was only one other user present! Only thing that can be improved is there's only one toilet, whereas there are 3 showers and you don't really have an area to freshen up, just a small sink.

Other than that, lovely gym!

author: Josh D.A
text: Have visited many AF outlets but this one spells HOME & is a sanctuary. Renovations in progress now though but that aside, i've had the pleasure of working out in Keppel's clean, organised & welcoming atmosphere. Manager & Staff are extremely knowledgeable & friendly. Also appreciate that there's no hard pushy selling but a very empathetic consultative approach by manager. Overall, refreshing experience compared to sterile commercial cookie-cutter feel of other gyms.

author: Maimunah Nokman
text:
Through the SPARK PT Starter Pack, I trained with Kal and was impressed by his knowledge and experience. After every session, I left the gym feeling accomplished and made sure I learnt something new each time. I appreciate how he focuses on functional strength training, which enhances mobility, balance, and injury prevention. Additionally, his approach of incorporating more free weights and bodyweight exercises into workouts is practical‚Äîsomething I can also apply when travelling or exercising in environments without large machines.

I appreciate the effort Kal takes to explain the workouts we are doing, as well as the plan he puts together for each session to ensure we are making the most of our time.

If you're someone looking to start a new exercise regimen or ease back into a workout routine, I highly recommend having a conversation with Kal. His experience and dedication to helping you reach your goals truly stand out!

author: K Daron
text:
Update 2023

This gym will charge an extra 20% if you are an existing member. The reason is due to inflation.

Other clubs has not increase the rates for existing regular members yet.

Please beware of this increase.

I would consider this gym as sub par. The new layout of the gym is terrible as the power rack and deadlift platform is cramped up in one corner.

Before 2023:

Good gym with incredible high ceilings and lighting

They have 2 Precor Racks and many benches

Barbells are Ziva Branded and weights are Ziva bumper plates and regular anytime fitness plates

Dumbbells ranges from 1-40kg

They also have fixed barbells ranging from 10-45kg

Basic gym machines are available

However, they do not have an in-house foam roller. They also do not have much variety of cable attachments and add-ons. Essential equipments that are missing: V-Bar & weighted dip belt.

Lighting is sharp and great with ground to ceiling windows that brings in lots of natural sunlight

Music selections could be better, usually the playlists are a little ‚Äútoo soft‚Äù for a proper strong workout

Downside is that they only have one toilet cubicle and 3 shower cubicle. The toilet cubicle is often smelly but i think that could be solved by leaving the door opened after using.

Overall a good gym with a nice atmosphere but has areas it can improve upon to be better

author: David Matupang
text:
14/02/2025: Many thanks, Adib, for your call and for providing me with the solution.
For those on Adroid wanting to know, please refer below:

Make sure that Google Pay/Google Wallet is set as the default wallet app.
Open the Settings app.
Tap "Connections", then tap "NFC and contactless payments", then tap "Contactless Payments".
Make sure that Google Pay is selected as the default payment service on the "Payment" tab.
Make sure that Google Wallet is selected in the "Others" tab.
Check if there is an AF App update available.
If there is one available, please install it.
Logout of the AF app, and after logging back in, please go to Profile and tap Gym Membership.
Next to Status, it should say Unlink Membership; tap that. Then tap Link Membership.
If it only gives the option to Link Membership, tap that instead.
Follow steps to verify and relink the membership.
Re-download the Access Pass
While in the AF app, please remove any passes that appear.
Logout of the app, sign back in, and try creating the Access Pass again. This should prompt the phone to give all necessary permissions.
Navigate to the Profile screen in the AF App by clicking the icon on the upper right-hand corner of the app.
Tap the "Add to Wallet" button that is displayed next to AF Access Pass.
If errors are encountered when attempting to add the Access Pass to their wallet, please cycle the method of data connection.
For example, try while using cellular data, and then while fully connected to Wifi.
Open Google Wallet and make sure "Smart Tap" is enabled.
¬∑

Open the Google Wallet app and tap on the Access Pass to open it.
The Google Wallet app should display the Access Pass as a card with their name on it. Tap the menu button in the upper right.
Check the toggle labeled "Hold near terminal to use". Enable the toggle if it is not already enabled.
